history.text: 84% on Rotten Tomatoes is a great score.
I loved this movie! I thought Christian Bale did an excellent job portraying a highly disturbed batman.
It got a good metascore rating as well
I loved the storyline of how Bruce Wayne becomes Batman.
I loved how they finally explored batmans origins, the story of how and why he became batman
The comic-book/real people type of movie like Batman Begins is super interesting.
I thought it added a lot of authenticity to the story anx made sense of a lot of things
It kind of pulled everything together to make a solid story plot.
I love the comic book movies, they are so cool
The other batman movies never explained why he became batman, abd i like that this one did
Batman is such a silent but superhero character
He was always m favorite superhero
Much better than the newer Batman movie

His psyche is extremely important to keep him as his own character
I do think batman was always one of the more honorable superheros, and more realistic and believable
